track_notes: Park in small space off the B5292 at NY 2271 2378. Leave the CP at the north end up the steps.  After that it is a simple case of following the path upwards.  It flattens and dips around 370m. Towards the top it gets quite steep on some loose scree, but is still simple to follow.

Total time (including ops): 3h 45m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Grisedale Pike Linear from Braithwaite. Aug 2022.

track_notes:
Parking available in the big layby or in the Noble Knott car park.  Follow waymarked Masmill Beck trail initially then continue over stile out of the forest to join main Grizedale Pike path.  Continue on well defined path to summit (steep and rocky near the summit).

Descend along path NE alongside remains of wall down to forest, then along forest track to visitor centre. Cafe, toilets, drinking water available.

From visitor centre follow C2C route initially then forest road to barrier and crossing with the tarmac road.  Cross road, up steel rooty path to forest road on south side and continue to rejoin Masmill Beck trail back to car park.
track_title: Circular route from Noble Knott via visitor centre
